NCH Software is a growing software development company with offices in
Colorado and Australia. Please visit www.nchsoftware.com to get an overview of
our software categories and 80+ products. Our Brisbane team is responsible for
our new Brisk line of cloud products.

We are seeking to employ a high energy individual to work with our cloud based
developers to make smart and user friendly front end pages and UI using HTML
and JavaScript.

This is a role where you will get to make much more than websites and will be
an active part of a team developing new cloud based apps. If you like the user
experience part of HTML and JavaScript this is your chance to really enjoy
making something users love.

Essential must-have requirements:

  * Excellent level of HTML 
  * Excellent level of JavaScript 
  * General knowledge of CSS 
  * Broad internet savvy and technology knowledge 
  * Ability to write clear text when required 
  * Must have energy and enthusiasm for everything online 

We are a company that takes the development of our products seriously, but you
will not see a suit or tie in the office. If you know HTML and JavaScript and
really enjoy making smart web pages and products with them you will find this
position rewarding.

No paperwork. Fewer meetings. No suits or ties.

Be part of a professional team in a growing company really making new stuff.

** *** This is a full time in office in person position. **

Salary will be competitive based depending on your commercial experience and
level of skills demonstrated.

To apply please use the Seek Apply button and provide your resume and a
covering letter with:

  * A short summary resume of your work history and references for each position. 
  * Indicate where you learned HTML and JavaScript and provide examples of work online. 
  * Please include your salary history or salary expectations. 
  * Please include your phone number and address. 

** To apply you must be able to attend in person for an interview. ** You need to have a right to work in Australia ** (you need to be a citizen or permanent resident - we can't sponsor foreign visas for this position or consider applicants who are not currently in Australia). **

Our Brisbane offices are located in River City Labs / the Precinct in
Fortitude Valley.

